<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Get Wrong</h2>

  <h3>Leaving Gaps at the Base</h3>
  <p>
    Even small openings allow pests in.
  </p>

  <h3>Installing Too Late</h3>
  <p>
    Pests may already be present.
  </p>

  <h3>Using Mesh That’s Too Wide</h3>
  <p>
    Smaller insects can pass through.
  </p>

  <h3>Not Securing Against Wind</h3>
  <p>
    Movement creates openings.
  </p>
</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>How This Fits Into Pest Management</h2>

  <p>
    Pop-up protectors are part of a preventive approach. They reduce pest pressure before it becomes a problem, making other control methods less necessary.
  </p>

  <p>
    They’re most effective when used early and consistently.
